Pope Leo XIV's fashion choices make waves, and many wonder what they mean
description: VATICAN CITY — When Pope Leo XIV stepped out on the central loggia of St. Peter's Basilica to greet the crowd for the first time after his May 8 election, liturgical fashion aficionados around the globe took note: Gone was the simple white cassock and silver cross favored by Pope Francis. Back was the red satin mozzetta shoulder cape, the burgundy stola with gold embroidery and a gold cross held by a double-stranded silken gold cord.

description: The International Plaza, 828 N. Clinton Ave., will host a special Latin American- and Caribbean-themed Father’s Day celebration at 1 p.m. Sunday, June 15 featuring live entertainment, music, and community games to honor the role fathers and father figures play in our community.The day’s lineup includes a performance by Mairy, along with music provided by DJ Franco.
